.el .ds Aq '
.TH dkp-serve 1  "serve 0.1.1" 
.SH NAME
dkp\-serve \- Start the pack as an MCP server (requires \-\-features mcp)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdkp serve\fR [\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-\-transport\fR] [\fB\-\-port\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-\-readonly\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-\-audience\fR] [\fB\-\-auth\-token\fR] [\fB\-\-log\-level\fR] [\fB\-\-allow\-unsigned\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIPACK\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Start the pack as an MCP server (requires \-\-features mcp)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR [default: plain]
Output format
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
plain: Human\-readable plain text (default)
.IP \(bu 2
table: Aligned table using comfy\-table
.IP \(bu 2
json: Pretty\-printed JSON
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-transport\fR \fI<TRANSPORT>\fR [default: stdio]
Transport mechanism: stdio | http
.TP
\fB\-\-port\fR \fI<PORT>\fR [default: 8734]
HTTP server port (when \-\-transport http)
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress informational output; print only results
.TP
\fB\-\-readonly\fR
Expose resources only; do not expose any tools
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Print debug info (schema paths, provider calls, etc.)
.TP
\fB\-\-audience\fR \fI<ID>\fR
Filter content to assets tagged for a specific audience profile
.TP
\fB\-\-auth\-token\fR \fI<TOKEN>\fR
Static bearer token for authentication
.TP
\fB\-\-log\-level\fR \fI<LEVEL>\fR [default: info]
Server log verbosity: debug | info | warn
.TP
\fB\-\-allow\-unsigned\fR
Allow running non\-WASM procedures from unsigned bundles (dev/testing only)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.TP
<\fIPACK\fR>
Path to the DKP bundle directory
.SH VERSION
v0.1.1
